    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, so my tomato plants are looking kind of weird. The leaves on the bottom of the plants are turning all yellow, but the new growth at the top looks fine. Do you know what might be going on with them? I'm worried I'm doing something wrong with the soil.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yellowing leaves on tomato plants can be a bit of a mystery, but I'm here to help you troubleshoot. It's possible that your plants are experiencing a condition called \"lower leaf drop,\" which is often caused by a lack of nutrients, especially iron, in the soil. You might want to consider getting a soil test to determine the nutrient levels in your soil. It's also worth checking for any signs of pests or diseases that could be causing the issue. \n\nYou know, it's a bit like when a group of younglings in a group of goblins are left behind while the rest of the tribe goes off to forage for food. The younglings might not be getting the nutrients they need to grow and thrive, just like your yellowing leaves. But, I'm sure it's not a case of goblin neglect on your part!",
